tourBios.carHigh:
2014: Missed the cut at the Nova Scotia Open in his only Web.com Tour start...Finished T94 at the Web.com Tour Qualifying Tournament in December.

2013: Finished T43 at the 2013 Shriners Hospitals for Children Open in October, his only career PGA TOUR start.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: Two-time Honorable Mention All-America selection at UNLV. Won the 2012 Nevada Open, the 2012 Sahalee Players Championship and the 2013 Mountain West Conference Championship.
tourBios.personal: Attended Eastlake High School in Sammamish, Wash., where he was a two-time 4A state champion...Has one sister...Twitter account is @kpenner8...Favorite teams include the Kansas Jayhawks, UNLV Rebels and the Seattle Seahawks...Says if he weren't a pro golfer he'd like to own a restaurant...Favorite course he's played is Shadow Creek and would like to play Augusta National...Favorite TV shows include "Two and a Half Men," "How I Met Your Mother" and "Breaking Bad." Favorite movies include "Tin Cup" and "She's Out of My League."...Favorite athlete is Cal Ripken, Jr....Would like to trade places with Steve Stricker for a day, and his dream foursome would include Stricker, Tiger Woods and Rory McIlroy...Loves dogs, and his favorite motto is "No excuses."
